1/4 teaspoon coriander 
1/2 teaspoon granulated garlic 
1/2 teaspoon granulated onion 
1/2 teaspoon tumeric
1 teaspoon curry powder 
1 teaspoon baharat curry 
1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika 
1/2 teaspoon cayenne 
Salt & pepper to taste 

Basmati rice 
2 teaspoon ghee or olive oil 
1 cinnamon stick 
1/8 teaspoon cardamom 
1/2 teaspoon cumin 
1/2 c peas 
2 c basmati rice
2 1/2 c water 
1/2 teaspoon turmeric in 2 t of water 

Garnish; fennel fronds, scallion curls, fresno chili & cilantro

@soulphil has been a dream of mine since I was 17 right around the time I started working at @redbirdla 👩🏽‍🍳 As a young cook I had all the aspirations of working under the best and creating something that belonged to me. Something that I could identify with whole heartedly. 

Some of my very first culinary lessons that related to real life teachable moments happened in and around this kitchen. I was green as ever, making a mess with my head in the clouds. Somethings don’t ever change.. 😩😂. But I literally entered adulthood here and every moment of my journey plays a major part in who I am today and how I represent for my culture. 

10 years later, Im living a full circle moment. Im beyond thrilled and honored to be hosting my very first SoulPhil brunch here in the garden 🥹 Where things thrive and are fruitful just like me ☀️🌱 It feels like a homecoming and Im elated to share this special moment with y’all! 

I hope to see all my TEECUPS on the west coast representing on August 27th! Click the link in my bio to get your tickets to a one of a kind SoulPhil moment 🎟️💛🥰

SoulPhil is a unique pop-up restaurant that is heart crafted by Chef Tiana Gee, a Filipina and Black Los Angeles native. SoulPhil is chef Tee’s way of celebrating her heritage through Filipino and soul food fusion. Chef Tee is dedicated to creating a memorable dining experience that highlights the rich and comforting flavors of soul food with the bold and aromatic elements of Filipino cuisine, using locally sourced ingredients. Chef Tee has had numerous successful pop ups in Los Angeles, New York and at Food and Wine’s Family Reunion fest in Virginia. Chef’s creation is the perfect highlight for fusion foods and a delicious way to get to know who she really is. “Her food tastes like colors”, is one of the best ways to describe what you will be getting a taste of at one of her soul crafted pop ups.

I feel so overwhelmed with love after this past weekend. Words cant express my gratitude towards @officialsheilajohnson & @chefkwameonwuachi for bringing us all together again to celebrate our lives, journeys, and connect through our culture. Thank you both for creating a space for us to completely be ourselves in, a space where we don’t have to over explain, or shrink to feel understood. Being immersed in this type of energy is so important to many of us. Not only did I learn so much through the stories that we all shared but I also gained new perspective. Thank you for shining light on the excellence within our community and reminding me that excellence is within reach for all of us. My heart & spirit feel rejuvenated. I left feeling a lot lighter than I came in and more inspired than ever before. My family for life! So much love 🖤♾️

Idk about y’all but for me, its feeling like reflection season.
Ive never been the type of person who expresses myself through social media but I just wanted to share something from my heart to my teecup gang. If theres ever any moment where you feel like all odds are against you and your walls are caving in, I encourage you to try your best to stay grounded and remember what it is that holds you together. For me thats always been my connection with food and my trust in the universe. No matter what Ive been through, Ive always kept at my love for cooking and never let anyone take that away from me. Whatever your divine passion is never give up on that vision. Trust your calling and know everything will fall into place. Stay on path and if its worth anything, if Im able to resurface after a storm.. you can too 🤍

Its giving fall 🍂 some of my favorite things about this season are fresh baked goods, snuggle food and gathering with all my loved the ones. 

I usually feel a little bittersweet about fall season, it’s just a reminder that the year is coming to an end, but it also allows me to take a look back and really appreciate all the blessings and lessons throughout the year and all that are about to come next. I know I’m probably not the only one who feels this way so when it comes to this season, I always make sure to keep my recipes, super comforting and soul hugging. I love every season in a different way but I feel like this fall in particular is meant for me to fall in love with myself all over again. So which ever of my Teecups need to hear this, make sure you love on yourself extra this season and fill your cup first or your belly.. lol 🥰 

I have some amazing recipes coming your way this season to get you guys ready for all of the fall feels. Click the link in my bio to subscribe to my YouTube channel and stay hip ✨🧡

Around the time I was 17, I was working as a cook and started to question what my food would look like if I were to open a restaurant..
